You&#39;re current control flow is as follows.

```java
if(selection == 1)
{
    if((selection &lt;= names.length)&amp;&amp;(selection &gt; 0))
    {
        System.out.println(&quot;yes&quot;);
    }

}

if(selection == 2)
{

}
else if(selection == 0)
{

}
else
{
    System.out.println(&quot;This option was not provided, please try again&quot;);
}
```

Thus, after the _&quot;yes&quot;_ message is printed, it will continue to the next set of conditional statements.

The solution is to add an _else_ keyword before the _selection == 2_ check.

