After adding `i` stars, you to add `5-i` plus sign

    int lineLength = 5;
    for (int i = 0; i &lt; lineLength; i++) {
        for (int j = 0; j &lt; i; j++) {
            System.out.print(&quot;* &quot;);
        }
        for (int j = 0; j &lt; lineLength - i; j++) {
            System.out.print(&quot;+ &quot;);
        }
        System.out.println();
    }

----

You can use `String.repeat` to simplify the code

    int lineLength = 5;
    for (int i = 0; i &lt; lineLength; i++) {
        System.out.println(&quot;* &quot;.repeat(i) + &quot;+ &quot;.repeat(lineLength - i));
    }

    for (int x = 0; x &lt; 5; x++) {
        for (int y = 0; y &lt; 5; y++) {
            System.out.print(x &gt; y ? &quot;* &quot; : &quot;+ &quot;);
        }
        System.out.println();
    }

You are probably going for something like this?

