`maven-surefire-plugin` automatically detect test engine based on your dependencies - but by default only **one** is used - Junit5 test framework has higer priority and it is used. 

This behavior was changed between 2.x and 3.x version of surefire.

https://maven.apache.org/surefire/maven-surefire-plugin/examples/junit-platform.html#provider-selection

If you have mixed JUnit 4 and 5 tests in your projects you need to add junit-vintage-engine to your dependencies

```xml
&lt;dependency&gt;
        &lt;groupId&gt;org.junit.vintage&lt;/groupId&gt;
        &lt;artifactId&gt;junit-vintage-engine&lt;/artifactId&gt;
        &lt;version&gt;&lt;!-- junit 5 version used in project --&gt;&lt;/version&gt;
        &lt;scope&gt;test&lt;/scope&gt;
&lt;/dependency&gt;
```

You can try updating the Maven Surefire Plugin configuration in your pom.xml as follows:

    &lt;plugin&gt;
        &lt;groupId&gt;org.apache.maven.plugins&lt;/groupId&gt;
        &lt;artifactId&gt;maven-surefire-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
        &lt;version&gt;3.1.2&lt;/version&gt;
        &lt;configuration&gt;
            &lt;testFailureIgnore&gt;true&lt;/testFailureIgnore&gt;
            &lt;properties&gt;
                &lt;configurationParameters&gt;
                    cucumber.publish.quiet=true
                    cucumber.plugin=json:target/cucumber/cucumber.json
                &lt;/configurationParameters&gt;
            &lt;/properties&gt;
        &lt;/configuration&gt;
    &lt;/plugin&gt;

This configuration sets the cucumber.plugin property to generate the desired JSON report file in the target/cucumber directory.

 - Also please remove the maven-cucumber-reporting plugin configuration since it is not necessary with the updated Surefire Plugin.
 - Modify your testRunnerClass to remove the JSON plugin configuration since it will now be handled by the Surefire Plugin as below:


plugin = {&quot;pretty&quot;, &quot;html:target/cucumber/simple-reports.html&quot;, &quot;junit:target/cucumber/cucumber.xml&quot;}

By making these changes, you should be able to run mvn clean test with the updated Surefire Plugin version and generate the correct JSON report file in the target/cucumber directory, along with the simple reports and JUnit XML report.

