answers.body_markdown:
I see several problems in the code in your question. Your use of [PreparedStatement][1] is wrong. You can&#39;t use the same index for each invocation of method [setString][2]. Also, according to the image you posted, some of the columns in database table `tabelle` have `int` data type and so method `setString` is probably not appropriate. You should also use [try-with-resources][3] to ensure that you close the `PreparedStatement`. Also, the database will only be updated if you call method [executeUpdate][4]. Consider the following: (Note that your code is not assigning a value to column `Tordifferenz` which will cause an error.)
```java
private void insert() {
    try (preparedStatement = connection.prepareStatement(query)) {
        preparedStatement.setString(1, vereinFid.getText());
        preparedStatement.setInt(2, Integer.parseInt(spieleFid.getText()));
        preparedStatement.setInt(3, Integer.parseInt(siegeFid.getText()));
        preparedStatement.setInt(4, Integer.parseInt(niederlagenFid.getText()));
        preparedStatement.setInt(5, Integer.parseInt(unentschiedenFid.getText()));
        preparedStatement.setInt(6, Integer.parseInt(toreFid.getText()));
        preparedStatement.setInt(7, Integer.parseInt(gegentoreFid.getText()));
        preparedStatement.setInt(8, Integer.parseInt(punkteFid.getText()));
        preparedStatement.executeUpdate();
    }
    catch (SQLException exception) {
        Logger.getLogger(AddTabelleController.class.getName()).log(Level.SEVERE, null, exception);
    }
}
```
Do you realize that your [SQL] UPDATE will update all rows in `tabelle` since it contains no WHERE clause?

In method `speichern` you are using [bitwise OR][5] instead of [logical OR][6].
```java
if (Verein.isEmpty()        ||
    Spiele.isEmpty()        ||
    Siege.isEmpty()         ||
    Niederlagen.isEmpty()   ||
    Unentschieden.isEmpty() ||
    Tore.isEmpty()          ||
    Gegentore.isEmpty()     ||
    Punkte.isEmpty())
```


  [1]: https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/jdbc/basics/prepared.html
  [2]: https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/17/docs/api/java.sql/java/sql/PreparedStatement.html#setString(int,java.lang.String)
  [3]: https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/essential/exceptions/tryResourceClose.html
  [4]: https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/17/docs/api/java.sql/java/sql/PreparedStatement.html#executeUpdate()
  [5]: https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/java/nutsandbolts/op3.html
  [6]: https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/java/nutsandbolts/operators.html

